title: NSW Flood warning issued at 11:49pm EDT
text: Home › Weather Warning Summary › Flood Warning - Clarence River Weather Warnings - Flood Warning - Clarence River   Meteorology, New South WalesInitial Flood Warning for the Clarence Riverat Grafton Issued at 11:49 pm EDT on Monday 20 March 2017Flood Warning Number: 1Up to 138 millimetres of rain has been recorded during the past 48 hours to4:00 pm Monday over the Clarence River valley. Rain has easing since 4:00 pmMonday. At this stage is not possible to predict flood peaks because of uncertaintyover how much more rain will fall.Clarence River:Minor flooding is predicted along the Clarence River at GraftonThe Clarence River at Grafton (Prince St) is likely to reach around 2.50 metresTuesday morning with minor flooding.Flood Safety Advice:FloodSafe advice is available at www.ses.nsw.gov.auFor emergency assistance call the SES on telephone number 132 500. For life threatening emergencies, call 000 immediately.Next issue:The next warning will be issued by 07:00 am EDT on Tuesday 21 March 2017.Latest River Heights:Nymboida River at Nymboida, 5.29, Rising, 11:10 PM MON 20/03/17Mann River at Mitchell, 1.12, Steady, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Boyd River at Broadmeadows, 3.26, Rising, 11:15 PM MON 20/03/17Clarence River at Tabulam, 0.87, Steady, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Clarence River at Baryulgil, 4.87, Steady, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Mann River at Jackadgery, 6.65, Rising, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Clarence River at Lilydale, 8.87, Rising, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Orara River at Glenreagh (Automatic Gauge), 4.36, Falling, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Clarence River at Grafton (Prince St), 2.00, Rising, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Clarence River at Ulmarra, 1.49, Steady, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17Clarence River at Maclean, 0.86, Steady, 11:00 PM MON 20/03/17This advice is also available by dialling 1300 659 218. Warning, rainfall andriver information are available at www.bom.gov.au/nsw/flood. The latest weatherforecast is available at www.bom.gov.au/nsw/forecasts. Go!
